sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global                          " table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>u_linux_cmdb_staging</collection><condition/><description/><filter_condition/><message/><name>CheckDiskUsage</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[checkDiskSpace(current);

function checkDiskSpace(currComp){
		var tmp = currComp.u__temp_usage____;
		var usr = currComp.u__usr_usage____;
		var varP = currComp.u__var_usage____;
		var diskUsed = currComp.u_disk_used__gb_;
		var diskAvail = currComp.u_disk_space__gb_;
	if(tmp > 90 || usr > 90 ||  varP > 90 || (diskUsed/diskAvail)>0.9){
		gs.log(currComp.name + " is running low on disk spacee");
		var checkOpenTickets= new GlideRecord('incident');
		checkOpenTickets.addEncodedQuery("short_descriptionSTARTSWITH"+currComp.u_name+"'s Disk Space is low^stateIN1");
		checkOpenTickets.query();
		if(!checkOpenTickets.getRowCount()>0){
			var gr= new GlideRecord('incident');
			gr.initialize();
			gr.cmdb_ci=current.sys_id;
			gr.short_description = currComp.u_name+"'s Disk Space is low";
			gr.assignment_group='d625dccec0a8016700a222a0f7900d06';
			gr.caller_id='88dd4196806402007f44ebef8b01221f';
			gr.category='Hardware';
			gr.work_notes="/var Usage: "+ varP + "% \n/tmp Usage: "+ tmp + "% \n/usr Usage: "+ usr + "% \n Disk Available: "+ diskAvail + "GB \n Disk Used: "+ diskUsed + "GB \n";
			gr.insert();
			gs.log("Log inc");
		}else{
			gs.log("current ticket open");
		}
	}
}]]></script><sys_created_by>chris.wilson</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-06-12 10:29:37</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global                          </sys_domain><sys_id>4fa954e280a402007f44ebef8b0122c4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>7</sys_mod_count><sys_overrides/><sys_updated_by>chris.wilson</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2015-06-12 11:01:38</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script><sys_app_file action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><customer_update>true</customer_update><publish_override/><replace_on_upgrade>false</replace_on_upgrade><restore/><sys_app display_value="Linux Discovery">6a17aef980e002007f44ebef8b0122ca</sys_app><sys_code>!!45T/</sys_code><sys_created_by>chris.wilson</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-06-12 10:29:37</sys_created_on><sys_id>8b6c502680a402007f44ebef8b012242</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CheckDiskUsage</sys_name><sys_parent display_value="Linux cmdb staging">04c6f38e802402007f44ebef8b012219</sys_parent><sys_path>!!43*/!!45T/</sys_path><sys_policy/><sys_source_deleted>false</sys_source_deleted><sys_source_id>4fa954e280a402007f44ebef8b0122c4</sys_source_id><sys_source_table>sys_script</sys_source_table><sys_type>code</sys_type><sys_update_name>sys_script_4fa954e280a402007f44ebef8b0122c4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>chris.wilson</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2015-06-12 11:01:38</sys_updated_on></sys_app_file></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_4fa954e280a402007f44ebef8b0122c4
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global                          " table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>u_linux_cmdb_staging</collection><condition/><description/><filter_condition/><message/><name>CheckDiskUsage</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[checkDiskSpace(current);

function checkDiskSpace(currComp){
		var tmp = currComp.u__temp_usage____;
		var usr = currComp.u__usr_usage____;
		var varP = currComp.u__var_usage____;
		var diskUsed = currComp.u_disk_used__gb_;
		var diskAvail = currComp.u_disk_space__gb_;
	if(tmp > 90 || usr > 90 ||  varP > 90 || (diskUsed/diskAvail)>0.9){
		gs.log(currComp.name + " is running low on disk spacee");
		var checkOpenTickets= new GlideRecord('incident');
		checkOpenTickets.addEncodedQuery("short_descriptionSTARTSWITH"+currComp.u_name+"'s Disk Space is low^stateIN1");
		checkOpenTickets.query();
		if(!checkOpenTickets.getRowCount()>0){
			var gr= new GlideRecord('incident');
			gr.initialize();
			gr.cmdb_ci=current.sys_id;
			gr.short_description = currComp.u_name+"'s Disk Space is low";
			gr.assignment_group='d625dccec0a8016700a222a0f7900d06';
			gr.caller_id='88dd4196806402007f44ebef8b01221f';
			gr.category='Hardware';
			gr.work_notes="/var Usage: "+ varP + "% \n/tmp Usage: "+ tmp + "% \n/usr Usage: "+ usr + "% \n Disk Available: "+ diskAvail + "GB \n Disk Used: "+ diskUsed + "GB \n";
			gr.insert();
			gs.log("Log inc");
		}else{
			gs.log("current ticket open");
		}
	}
}]]></script><sys_created_by>chris.wilson</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-06-12 10:29:37</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global                          </sys_domain><sys_id>4fa954e280a402007f44ebef8b0122c4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>7</sys_mod_count><sys_overrides/><sys_updated_by>chris.wilson</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2015-06-12 11:01:38</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script><sys_app_file action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><customer_update>true</customer_update><publish_override/><replace_on_upgrade>false</replace_on_upgrade><restore/><sys_app display_value="Linux Discovery">6a17aef980e002007f44ebef8b0122ca</sys_app><sys_code>!!45T/</sys_code><sys_created_by>chris.wilson</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-06-12 10:29:37</sys_created_on><sys_id>8b6c502680a402007f44ebef8b012242</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CheckDiskUsage</sys_name><sys_parent display_value="Linux cmdb staging">04c6f38e802402007f44ebef8b012219</sys_parent><sys_path>!!43*/!!45T/</sys_path><sys_policy/><sys_source_deleted>false</sys_source_deleted><sys_source_id>4fa954e280a402007f44ebef8b0122c4</sys_source_id><sys_source_table>sys_script</sys_source_table><sys_type>code</sys_type><sys_update_name>sys_script_4fa954e280a402007f44ebef8b0122c4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>chris.wilson</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2015-06-12 11:01:38</sys_updated_on></sys_app_file></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global                          " table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>cmdb_ci_computer</collection><condition/><description/><filter_condition table="cmdb_ci_computer">osNOT LIKEWindows^os_versionISNOTEMPTY^EQ<item endquery="false" field="os" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="NOT LIKE" or="false" value="Windows"/><item endquery="false" field="os_version" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="ISNOTEMPTY" or="false" value=""/><item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><message/><name>CheckOSVersion</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[checkVersionAllowed(current);
function checkVersionAllowed(currComp){
	var versions = new GlideRecord("u_acceptable_os_version");
	versions.addEncodedQuery("u_os_versionSTARTSWITH"+currComp.os_version);
		gs.log(currComp.os_version);
	versions.query();
	if(versions.getRowCount()==0){
		//log call
		gs.log(currComp.os_version);
		var checkOpenTickets= new GlideRecord('incident');
		checkOpenTickets.addEncodedQuery("short_descriptionSTARTSWITH"+currComp.name+"'s kernel is outdated^stateIN1");
		checkOpenTickets.query();
		if(!checkOpenTickets.getRowCount()>0){
			var gr= new GlideRecord('incident');
			gr.initialize();
			gr.cmdb_ci=current.sys_id;
			gr.short_description = currComp.name + "'s kernel is outdated";
			gr.assignment_group='d625dccec0a8016700a222a0f7900d06';
			gr.caller_id='88dd4196806402007f44ebef8b01221f';
			gr.category='Hardware';
			gr.insert();
			
			gs.log("Log inc");
		}else{
			gs.log("current ticket open");
		}
	}else{
		gs.log("Version upto date");
	}
}
	]]></script><sys_created_by>chris.wilson</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-06-11 18:51:47</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global                          </sys_domain><sys_id>5a450d16806402007f44ebef8b01227a</sys_id><sys_mod_count>21</sys_mod_count><sys_overrides/><sys_updated_by>chris.wilson</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2015-06-11 20:12:22</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script><sys_app_file action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><customer_update>true</customer_update><publish_override/><replace_on_upgrade>false</replace_on_upgrade><restore/><sys_app display_value="Linux Discovery">6a17aef980e002007f44ebef8b0122ca</sys_app><sys_code>!!44,/</sys_code><sys_created_by>chris.wilson</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-06-11 18:51:47</sys_created_on><sys_id>55c50d16806402007f44ebef8b012283</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CheckOSVersion</sys_name><sys_parent display_value="Computer">59dc4819203221007f441083a8e0b309</sys_parent><sys_path>!!$,O/!!44,/</sys_path><sys_policy/><sys_source_deleted>false</sys_source_deleted><sys_source_id>5a450d16806402007f44ebef8b01227a</sys_source_id><sys_source_table>sys_script</sys_source_table><sys_type>code</sys_type><sys_update_name>sys_script_5a450d16806402007f44ebef8b01227a</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>chris.wilson</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2015-06-11 20:12:22</sys_updated_on></sys_app_file></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global                          " table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>cmdb_ci_computer</collection><condition/><description/><filter_condition table="cmdb_ci_computer">osNOT LIKEWindows^os_versionISNOTEMPTY^EQ<item endquery="false" field="os" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="NOT LIKE" or="false" value="Windows"/><item endquery="false" field="os_version" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="ISNOTEMPTY" or="false" value=""/><item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><message/><name>CheckOSVersion</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[checkVersionAllowed(current);
function checkVersionAllowed(currComp){
	var versions = new GlideRecord("u_acceptable_os_version");
	versions.addEncodedQuery("u_os_versionSTARTSWITH"+currComp.os_version);
		gs.log(currComp.os_version);
	versions.query();
	if(versions.getRowCount()==0){
		//log call
		gs.log(currComp.os_version);
		var checkOpenTickets= new GlideRecord('incident');
		checkOpenTickets.addEncodedQuery("short_descriptionSTARTSWITH"+currComp.name+"'s kernel is outdated^stateIN1");
		checkOpenTickets.query();
		if(!checkOpenTickets.getRowCount()>0){
			var gr= new GlideRecord('incident');
			gr.initialize();
			gr.cmdb_ci=current.sys_id;
			gr.short_description = currComp.name + "'s kernel is outdated";
			gr.assignment_group='d625dccec0a8016700a222a0f7900d06';
			gr.caller_id='88dd4196806402007f44ebef8b01221f';
			gr.category='Hardware';
			gr.insert();
			
			gs.log("Log inc");
		}else{
			gs.log("current ticket open");
		}
	}else{
		gs.log("Version upto date");
	}
}
	]]></script><sys_created_by>chris.wilson</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-06-11 18:51:47</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global                          </sys_domain><sys_id>5a450d16806402007f44ebef8b01227a</sys_id><sys_mod_count>21</sys_mod_count><sys_overrides/><sys_updated_by>chris.wilson</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2015-06-11 20:12:22</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script><sys_app_file action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><customer_update>true</customer_update><publish_override/><replace_on_upgrade>false</replace_on_upgrade><restore/><sys_app display_value="Linux Discovery">6a17aef980e002007f44ebef8b0122ca</sys_app><sys_code>!!44,/</sys_code><sys_created_by>chris.wilson</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-06-11 18:51:47</sys_created_on><sys_id>55c50d16806402007f44ebef8b012283</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>CheckOSVersion</sys_name><sys_parent display_value="Computer">59dc4819203221007f441083a8e0b309</sys_parent><sys_path>!!$,O/!!44,/</sys_path><sys_policy/><sys_source_deleted>false</sys_source_deleted><sys_source_id>5a450d16806402007f44ebef8b01227a</sys_source_id><sys_source_table>sys_script</sys_source_table><sys_type>code</sys_type><sys_update_name>sys_script_5a450d16806402007f44ebef8b01227a</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>chris.wilson</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2015-06-11 20:12:22</sys_updated_on></sys_app_file></record_update>
